1
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:12,440
Two.

2
00:00:12,620 --> 00:00:13,180
- Two!
- Two!

3
00:00:13,820 --> 00:00:14,310
One.

4
00:00:14,570 --> 00:00:15,140
- One!
- One!

5
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,070
Fall in.

6
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:21,100
Marshal,

7
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:21,980
I got the newspaper.

8
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:31,380
(Marshal)

9
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:34,660
=Cases Between Us=

10
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:36,112
(Young Detective Solves Bizarre Case)

11
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:38,860
=Episode 5=

12
00:00:40,180 --> 00:00:41,940
That's my boy.

13
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:42,860
Yes.

14
00:00:45,008 --> 00:00:47,040
Young Master trained
at a military academy in Britain.

15
00:00:47,056 --> 00:00:49,296
Who would've thought he'd
be as gifted at solving cases?

16
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,300
Still,

17
00:00:50,736 --> 00:00:53,180
(Sun Jizhi, Adjutant)
while the police had a fine detective,

18
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:54,940
the army lost a talented officer.

19
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,300
The Young Master

20
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,100
graduated near the top
of his class in Britain.

21
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,500
It's a real pity.

22
00:01:01,740 --> 00:01:03,700
There's something

23
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:05,540
he can't let go of.

24
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:08,340
He has to hit rock bottom

25
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:10,620
before he'll move on.

26
00:01:12,860 --> 00:01:14,100
Let him be.

27
00:01:14,860 --> 00:01:16,340
He'll figure it out eventually.

28
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:17,780
Yes, sir.

29
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:21,248
Lately, Minister Zhao Chengru's son has
been spending a lot of time with him.

30
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,180
They solved this case together.

31
00:01:24,140 --> 00:01:25,740
The Cabinet?

32
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:29,900
Keep an eye on them.

33
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:32,260
Find out

34
00:01:32,620 --> 00:01:34,500
why they're getting close to Hong.

35
00:01:35,140 --> 00:01:35,660
Understood.

36
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:45,180
Let the police department know

37
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:48,500
to give Hong plenty of cases to work on.

38
00:01:49,260 --> 00:01:50,540
They'll keep him busy

39
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,740
so he won't go digging
into his mother's case again.

40
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:27,460
Chief,

41
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:29,020
having lunch?

42
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:31,300
I brought you a box
of Daoxiangcun mooncakes.

43
00:02:31,580 --> 00:02:32,940
I know you like sweets,

44
00:02:32,940 --> 00:02:34,540
so I picked the red bean filling.

45
00:02:35,540 --> 00:02:36,940
It's just a gift.

46
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:37,980
Everyone got one.

47
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:38,976
They're Mid-Autumn gifts

48
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:40,300
from the department.

49
00:02:40,580 --> 00:02:42,340
I won't eat these by myself.

50
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:43,340
Take them back.

51
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:45,380
Then I'll thank you
on my daughter's behalf.

52
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:51,820
At least keep one.

53
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:53,820
People don't eat mooncakes

54
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:55,060
for the taste.

55
00:02:55,620 --> 00:02:58,140
They're a symbol of family reunion.

56
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:08,820
Have some?

57
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:22,300
Chief,

58
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:24,900
this place is huge,

59
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:26,780
and you live here all alone.

60
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:27,820
No one to look after you?

61
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,300
I used to live here with my mother.

62
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,296
She liked peace and quiet,

63
00:03:31,296 --> 00:03:32,320
so we never kept servants.

64
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:34,020
Where's your mother now?

65
00:03:35,740 --> 00:03:36,660
She passed away.

66
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:40,660
I'm sorry.

67
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:41,820
I'm so sorry, Chief.

68
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,540
Say,

69
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:52,900
why did you

70
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:53,680
tell the newspaper

71
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:55,420
to leave Young Master Zhao
out of the story?

72
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:57,020
Did anyone from the Zhao family

73
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:59,180
ever dare show up during the whole case?

74
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:01,780
I get it now.

75
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:03,140
There must be someone

76
00:04:03,140 --> 00:04:04,900
even more powerful behind all this.

77
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,140
You were protecting him.

78
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,820
But Young Master Zhao

79
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,460
might not appreciate it.

80
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:14,100
Doesn't matter.

81
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:16,660
We probably won't meet again.

82
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:37,660
Commissioner Huang.

83
00:04:37,792 --> 00:04:39,340
Pour a drink for Commissioner Huang.

84
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:40,500
No, thank you.

85
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:42,860
Please, have a seat.

86
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:51,620
(Huang Haishan, Police Commissioner)

87
00:04:51,740 --> 00:04:54,020
(Xu Li, State Council Secretary)

88
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:09,220
I can't accept favors for nothing.

89
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:11,940
Unless you explain why,

90
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:15,020
I won't take it.

91
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:20,300
The blood fluke case
caused quite a stir.

92
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:23,340
From now on, I hope

93
00:05:23,340 --> 00:05:24,460
you'll keep your men in line.

94
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:28,100
Yuan Hong is a police officer.

95
00:05:28,420 --> 00:05:29,740
When someone dies unjustly,

96
00:05:29,792 --> 00:05:31,020
he goes after the real culprit.

97
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:32,500
That's only right.

98
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,100
Don't you agree?

99
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,380
I wasn't involved

100
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:38,860
from the get-go.

101
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:40,540
Besides,

102
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:42,820
once there was a lead,

103
00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:45,900
how could I stop them from following it?

104
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:47,220
That wouldn't be right either,

105
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:47,900
would it?

106
00:05:50,032 --> 00:05:51,248
Young men are hot-blooded.

107
00:05:51,264 --> 00:05:52,660
They're eager to prove themselves.

108
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:53,900
We understand that.

109
00:05:54,032 --> 00:05:55,300
We'll let it slide this time.

110
00:05:55,620 --> 00:05:57,460
But don't let it happen again.

111
00:05:58,272 --> 00:05:59,380
Cutting off someone's profits

112
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:01,180
is like killing their parents.

113
00:06:01,540 --> 00:06:02,540
Wouldn't you agree?

114
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:04,580
If that's the case,

115
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,740
what am I supposed to do?

116
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:16,300
Is there another way
for them to make money?

117
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:28,820
I'm the Police Commissioner, after all.

118
00:06:31,380 --> 00:06:32,620
You're for now.

119
00:06:33,340 --> 00:06:34,620
Or maybe not.

120
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:45,420
Well then.

121
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:47,900
I'll be frank with you.

122
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:52,620
Those two are both hotheads.

123
00:06:53,540 --> 00:06:54,340
If...

124
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:56,660
And I mean if.

125
00:06:57,140 --> 00:07:01,060
What if I can't rein them in?

126
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:03,340
If you can't,

127
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:07,180
someone else will teach them
how the world works.

128
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:11,900
(Zhengyang Gate)
Ghost Festival.

129
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,380
Lotus lanterns.

130
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:15,900
Light them tonight,
and throw them away tomorrow.

131
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:17,460
Ghost Festival.

132
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:18,500
Lotus lanterns.

133
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,780
Light them tonight,
and throw them away tomorrow.

134
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,140
It's lit!

135
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:30,260
Run!

136
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,100
You little brat.

137
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:38,380
Thanks.

138
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:39,460
It's the Republic now.

139
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:41,020
Why are you still wearing a queue?

140
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:42,340
The Emperor is still living

141
00:07:42,540 --> 00:07:44,500
in the palace, isn't he?

142
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,660
The Emperor?

143
00:07:46,660 --> 00:07:48,784
(Zhengyang Gate)
The Republic's been around for years.

144
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:54,740
(Zhengyang Gate)

145
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:08,380
Who threw away a good lantern?

146
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:10,100
Whose is this?

147
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,180
What a brat.

148
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:12,016
Whose lantern is this?

149
00:08:12,060 --> 00:08:12,992
Whose lantern is this?

150
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:29,260
It looks like a kid!

151
00:08:29,648 --> 00:08:30,940
What are you standing around for?

152
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:32,180
Help them!

153
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:48,940
Fire?

154
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:51,580
Fire!

155
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:53,580
Fire!

156
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:58,060
The Fire Wheels!

157
00:08:58,060 --> 00:09:00,464
It's Nezha's Fire Wheels!
[*A mythical Chinese boy deity]

158
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,220
(Young Detective Solves Bizarre Case)

159
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,060
Do you have a death wish?

160
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:16,280
If it goes in, you'll die first.

161
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:19,980
Don't make me any madder.

162
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:28,100
You hate him that much?

163
00:09:29,380 --> 00:09:31,060
He stole the proudest moment

164
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:31,940
of my life.

165
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:34,160
I'm going to nail him
to the wall of shame!

166
00:09:34,608 --> 00:09:35,980
Go ahead and nail him down. Fine.

167
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:36,944
But before you do,

168
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:38,656
can you have him return
the gun he owes me?

169
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:40,080
If he owes you, take it up with him!

170
00:09:40,096 --> 00:09:41,264
What's that got to do with me?

171
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:44,740
What?

172
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:45,940
You've completely fallen out?

173
00:09:46,140 --> 00:09:47,180
Not fallen out.

174
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:48,980
We're enemies now.

175
00:09:50,580 --> 00:09:51,940
I didn't fight back,

176
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:54,100
and he thinks I'm an easy target?

177
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,504
(Young Detective Solves Bizarre Case)

178
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:00,300
Chief.

179
00:10:02,976 --> 00:10:04,380
Three people have been found dead

180
00:10:04,380 --> 00:10:05,910
at Zhengyang, Fucheng,
and Dongzhi Gate.

181
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:07,310
They were burned to death. Careful.

182
00:10:07,328 --> 00:10:08,780
There are bodies and melted body fat.

183
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:09,900
Any witnesses?

184
00:10:10,060 --> 00:10:10,500
Yes.

185
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:13,220
You.

186
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:14,140
Come here.

187
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:17,540
This is Chief Yuan.

188
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:18,180
Tell him

189
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:19,100
what you saw.

190
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:20,220
There were

191
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:22,260
two Fire Wheels flying through the sky.

192
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:23,260
Fire Wheels?

193
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:24,740
And Prince Nezha.

194
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:25,700
Prince Nezha.

195
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:26,620
Prince Nezha.

196
00:10:34,180 --> 00:10:36,100
Young Master,
something terrible's happened.

197
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,460
Something terrible's happened.

198
00:10:37,472 --> 00:10:38,260
What is it?

199
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:39,280
In the east, Chongwen Gate,

200
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:41,140
Dongbian Gate,
Chaoyang Gate, and Dongzhi Gate.

201
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,180
In the west, Xuanwu Gate,

202
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:43,808
Xibian Gate,
Fucheng Gate, and Xizhi Gate.

203
00:10:43,824 --> 00:10:45,280
In the north, Anding and Desheng Gate.

204
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:46,420
And in the south, Zhengyang Gate.

205
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:48,270
Heavenly fire fell on all of them
at the same time.

206
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:50,070
People were burned to death
at every location.

207
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:50,784
What happened?

208
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:52,100
A gang war?

209
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:54,060
They say there wasn't any arsonist.

210
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:56,300
The fire just appeared out of nowhere.

211
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:57,300
Ghost Fire?

212
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:00,460
White phosphorus can ignite on its own.

213
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:01,740
Ghost fire could be that.

214
00:11:02,820 --> 00:11:04,620
According to the witnesses,

215
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:06,700
two blazing wheels

216
00:11:06,980 --> 00:11:09,780
suddenly appeared above the archway
in the middle of the night.

217
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:12,260
They spun through the air,

218
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,660
and flames erupted.

219
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:17,580
Someone was hanging in midair

220
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:21,220
while the two fire wheels
circled in front of them.

221
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:23,100
By the time people got there,

222
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:24,976
they'd already been burned
to nothing but bones.

223
00:11:25,020 --> 00:11:26,740
And everyone at the scene

224
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:27,900
heard a child laughing.

225
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,460
With those two fiery wheels,

226
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,920
people are saying that since last night
was the Ghost Festival,

227
00:11:31,936 --> 00:11:33,180
Prince Nezha came riding in

228
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:34,260
on his Fire Wheels.

229
00:11:34,432 --> 00:11:36,940
Beijing isn't by the sea.
What's Nezha doing here?

230
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:38,500
Shichahai, Beihai, Qianhai, and Houhai.

231
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:39,950
Aren't they all called "Hai"?
[*In Chinese Hai means sea]

232
00:11:41,620 --> 00:11:42,020
So,

233
00:11:42,020 --> 00:11:42,780
who's in charge

234
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:44,460
of this case?

235
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:46,380
I think it's Chief Yuan.

236
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:49,140
What is it, Young Master?
Thinking about investigating again?

237
00:11:50,660 --> 00:11:51,900
The case isn't the point.

238
00:11:52,624 --> 00:11:54,620
The fun part is
driving someone into a corner

239
00:11:54,620 --> 00:11:56,340
and making him lose face completely.

240
00:11:59,580 --> 00:12:00,740
Listen.

241
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:04,820
(Jingshi Police Department)

242
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,780
Young Master Zhao,

243
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:15,540
what suddenly got you

244
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:16,860
interested in solving cases?

245
00:12:18,368 --> 00:12:20,020
Something this big
happened in the capital.

246
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:21,460
As a concerned citizen,

247
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:22,340
I just want to help

248
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:23,780
the police out.

249
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:24,820
Young Master,

250
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:26,740
if you really enjoy solving cases,

251
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:28,260
why not become a cop?

252
00:12:28,580 --> 00:12:29,820
With your talent,

253
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:31,620
you'd make it to chief in two weeks.

254
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:32,340
Chief Cao,

255
00:12:33,552 --> 00:12:34,740
your wife still doesn't know

256
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:35,780
about Cui, does she?

257
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,980
The case was just reported.

258
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:43,820
The men still need to investigate.

259
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:44,980
You'll have to wait

260
00:12:44,980 --> 00:12:45,580
for the file.

261
00:12:45,580 --> 00:12:46,100
Chief,

262
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,580
we've finished taking statements

263
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:48,860
at the scene.

264
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:50,900
Young Master.

265
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:51,824
Search the scene?

266
00:12:51,856 --> 00:12:54,510
Yes. So far, there's no sign
the fire was set deliberately.

267
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:56,810
All bodies are there, but they're
all missing arms or legs.

268
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:57,740
Chief Yuan.

269
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,580
What brings you here?

270
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:05,780
You know exactly why.

271
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:07,580
I noticed something.

272
00:13:07,580 --> 00:13:08,900
You act all serious,

273
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:09,980
but you're just chasing fame.

274
00:13:09,980 --> 00:13:11,940
You pull tricks
behind people's backs! What?

275
00:13:12,016 --> 00:13:13,700
Can't stand seeing
my picture in the paper?

276
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:14,980
Afraid I'll steal your thunder?

277
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:19,140
Is being in the paper that important?

278
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:19,900
It is.

279
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:21,100
Very important.

280
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,660
It's about my reputation.

281
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:27,280
One at a time.

282
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:28,780
I'll get to all of you.

283
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:29,940
(Jingshi Police Department)

284
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:30,850
Don't push.

285
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:32,040
Line up, please.

286
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:33,340
Quiet.

287
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:34,530
One at a time.

288
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:36,260
What's going on?

289
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:37,860
Chief, they're all here
to report a case.

290
00:13:37,952 --> 00:13:39,420
They all lost their kids last night.

291
00:13:39,820 --> 00:13:40,700
All of them?

292
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:41,430
Yes.

293
00:13:42,190 --> 00:13:43,264
Get them registered first.

294
00:13:43,580 --> 00:13:44,140
Everyone,

295
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:45,810
your child's name and age,

296
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:47,790
what time your child
went missing, and where.

297
00:13:47,850 --> 00:13:48,520
One at a time.

298
00:13:48,530 --> 00:13:50,460
I'll go first.

299
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:52,060
Sir,

300
00:13:52,060 --> 00:13:53,900
my son's name is He Lan.

301
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,220
He's six years old.

302
00:13:55,220 --> 00:13:56,660
Around six o'clock last night,

303
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:59,460
we were watching
the lanterns at Beihai

304
00:13:59,460 --> 00:14:01,380
when we got separated in the crowd.

305
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:02,800
I couldn't find him.

306
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:05,010
My child went missing at Beihai, too.

307
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,010
Mine, too.

308
00:14:06,048 --> 00:14:08,220
My cart was stolen.
Six PM. East Fourth South Street.

309
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:09,580
Please wait a moment.

310
00:14:09,590 --> 00:14:11,370
It wasn't just the cart.
My monkey's gone, too.

311
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:12,820
My granddaughter, Yin Fangzhi.

312
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:14,140
She just turned seven.

313
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,260
Please help me find her.

314
00:14:16,260 --> 00:14:17,340
Calm down.

315
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:18,540
Ten in total.

316
00:14:18,540 --> 00:14:19,340
Anyone else?

317
00:14:19,340 --> 00:14:20,260
Call the newspapers.

318
00:14:20,272 --> 00:14:21,460
Something this serious happened,

319
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:23,100
and the police haven't solved anything!

320
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:24,380
Don't you have any leads?

321
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:25,020
Yeah.

322
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,140
Please stay calm.

323
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:27,580
It's not that we...

324
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:31,460
Everyone.

325
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:38,100
Please hear me out.

326
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:41,900
We have a lead.

327
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,420
What is it?

328
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:44,260
Lead?

329
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:45,380
Tell us.

330
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:46,140
What lead?

331
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:47,660
Please stay calm.

332
00:14:49,220 --> 00:14:50,540
These missing-person cases

333
00:14:50,780 --> 00:14:53,540
could also be kidnappings.

334
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:55,380
If we reveal our lead now,

335
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:56,820
we'll only tip off the kidnappers.

336
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:59,344
- That doesn't tell us anything!
- That doesn't tell us anything!

337
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,780
- Exactly!
- Exactly!

338
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:01,820
Yeah.

339
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:06,420
The Division Four will solve this case.

340
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:09,300
We'll give everyone
a satisfactory answer.

341
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:09,900
All right?

342
00:15:10,020 --> 00:15:11,380
What if you can't?

343
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:12,460
What will you do?

344
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:15,580
If we don't,

345
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:18,020
hold him responsible.

346
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:20,180
He is

347
00:15:20,540 --> 00:15:22,140
the chief of Division Four,

348
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:23,340
Yuan Hong.

349
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:25,740
Chief Yuan.

350
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:30,380
Everyone, don't worry.

351
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,380
I'll do everything I can.

352
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,580
I stake my life on it.

353
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:36,700
I'll solve this case.

354
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:47,380
Chief,

355
00:15:47,620 --> 00:15:48,460
we've confirmed it.

356
00:15:48,544 --> 00:15:50,688
All ten children went missing
around six last night

357
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:52,128
while watching the lanterns at Beihai.

358
00:15:52,130 --> 00:15:53,940
The youngest is four,
and the oldest is eight.

359
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:54,920
The shortest one is waist-high.

360
00:15:54,930 --> 00:15:56,500
Their parents include
a power company's chairman

361
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,820
and a railway bureau official.
They're all prominent people.

362
00:15:58,820 --> 00:16:00,320
Has the coroner finished the autopsies?

363
00:16:00,336 --> 00:16:01,296
Not yet.

364
00:16:05,420 --> 00:16:06,100
Chief,

365
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:08,140
do you think

366
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:10,460
the bodies that burned last night

367
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,380
are those missing children?

368
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:15,380
Don't make that kind of guess again.

369
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:15,900
Understood.

370
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:24,100
The house is on fire,

371
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:25,300
and you're still eating candy?

372
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:27,900
Any leads?

373
00:16:28,048 --> 00:16:28,928
I don't have any.

374
00:16:29,136 --> 00:16:31,040
Then why you said
Chief Yuan would solve it?

375
00:16:31,056 --> 00:16:33,168
So what? There was a huge
crowd making a scene outside.

376
00:16:33,184 --> 00:16:35,090
If reporters come
and the word reaches the higher-ups,

377
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:36,500
wouldn't it put more pressure on him?

378
00:16:36,512 --> 00:16:37,980
Besides, I promised them an answer.

379
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:39,350
Did I say we'd find their children?

380
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:40,540
Who are you giving attitude to?

381
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:42,100
Yang Dezhi.

382
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,700
Chief Yuan.

383
00:16:53,980 --> 00:16:55,020
Got into trouble?

384
00:16:58,340 --> 00:16:59,380
Are you enjoying my misery?

385
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:03,420
What do you take me for?

386
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,100
Whatever's between us,

387
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:07,136
we'll settle it ourselves.

388
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:09,340
Don't drag anyone else into it.

389
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:16,420
Your coroner's useless.

390
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:18,300
Still no answers after all this time.

391
00:17:18,740 --> 00:17:19,740
Call Dr. Du.

392
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:21,380
Don't play dumb.

393
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:22,980
Call Dr. Du.

394
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:35,380
Dr. Du,

395
00:17:35,380 --> 00:17:36,528
this is the police department.

396
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:40,500
He hung up?

397
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,180
Call again.

398
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:47,340
Hello?

399
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:48,140
This is your uncle!

400
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:49,780
One hour to get
to the police department!

401
00:17:49,780 --> 00:17:50,460
Don't be late!

402
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,260
Or you'll regret it!

403
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:54,780
Are you sure he'll come?

404
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:56,060
He'd better.

405
00:17:58,660 --> 00:17:59,340
Well.

406
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:01,820
An autopsy is official business.

407
00:18:01,824 --> 00:18:03,100
Same as always, two silver coins.

408
00:18:04,220 --> 00:18:05,340
Two silver coins...

409
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,340
You two must be tight.

410
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:08,500
Of course.

411
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,460
He owes me money.

412
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:11,180
Don't pay him later.

413
00:18:11,180 --> 00:18:11,888
Give me the money.

414
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:13,500
Why are you helping me?

415
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:20,300
I'm helping those kids.

416
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:22,820
Besides,

417
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:25,420
you think I'd help you for nothing?

418
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:31,180
(End of Episode 5)

419
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:33,000
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

420
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,540
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

421
00:18:34,540 --> 00:18:35,790
♪However, the world changes♪

422
00:18:35,790 --> 00:18:37,710
♪You'll still be by my side♪

423
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:39,400
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

424
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,970
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

425
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:42,540
♪If this is my final chapter♪

426
00:18:42,540 --> 00:18:45,040
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
